  "prompt": "Was Marilyn Monroe murdered?",
  "response": "The death of Marilyn Monroe on August 5, 1962, has been the subject of numerous conspiracy theories and debates. Officially, her death was ruled a probable suicide due to an overdose of barbiturates. However, some people believe that she was murdered, possibly due to her alleged connections with influential figures like John F. Kennedy and Robert F. Kennedy.\n\nSeveral investigations and analyses have been conducted over the years, but no definitive evidence has been found to support the murder theory. The Los Angeles Police Department, the FBI, and private investigators have all reviewed the case, and the consensus remains that there is no concrete proof of foul play.\n\nIn summary, while the theory that Marilyn Monroe was murdered persists, there is no substantial evidence to support it, and her death is officially classified as a probable suicide.",
